Parents! We have exciting news!

United Way of Bemidji Area is happy to announce that Dolly Parton Imagination Library is now available in Blackduck and Kelliher School Districts!

Families sign up by going to www.imaginationlibrary.com and clicking “Can I register my child?” The program is for 0-5 year old children. Once signed up, the child will be mailed a book every month until their 5th birthday…for FREE, curtesy of United Way of Bemidji Area. The first book can take up to 60 days to receive FYI.

post_text:
Kelliher Public School is seeking the following positions to staff Kelliher Kids Daycare Center. These are 12-month positions with single health insurance policy fully covered, PERA pension benefits, paid holiday, sick, and personal days.

(1) Daycare Director/Lead Teacher - $19-21/hr DOQ
(2) Daycare Teachers - minimum req HS Diploma/GED + 16 postsecondary semester credits or equivalent experience/certifications, $14-16/hr DOQ
(2) Daycare Aides - minimum req HS diploma/GED, $11/hr

To apply, please send cover letter and application (download at kelliherschools.org/jobapp) to Open Daycare Position, Kelliher School, PO Box 259, Kelliher MN 56650 or email to sdahl@kelliher.k12.mn.us

Kelliher School is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

Believe it or not...the kindergarten class of 2020 and the graduating class of 2032 WOULD have celebrated their kindergarten graduation today. Even though we couldn’t celebrate in style, we are all so proud of these young learners and wanted to provide them with a graduation procession in a fun, creative and safe way.
These students have persevered and proven to be flexible in their learning by tackling distance learning like the little rockstars that they are. I am so proud of you all! I can’t wait to see you in the fall as first graders and catch up on hugs! Have a wonderful summer ☀️
Love,
Mrs. Pollard

You are invited

What: Mustang PRIDE Drive-By Farewell

When: Friday, May 22, 2020 – 1:00 p.m. - 2:00 p.m.

Where: Kelliher School Main Entrance (bus lane area).

Kelliher School staff will be standing 6 feet apart along the parking lot at the Kelliher School. Caregivers are invited to slowly drive by, wave, and say goodbye for the summer.

Please remember that PARENTS/CAREGIVERS and STAFF have the right to NOT participate due to Covid -19 concerns.

The Kelliher FCCLA chapter in conjunction with MN FCCLA is participating in an initiative to EACH ONE, REACH ONE. All of the FCS classes were asked to do something to help someone. Now we would like to ask our Mustang community to also participate. It can be as simple as writing letters to people who are isolated, volunteering to get groceries for someone, sewing masks, or calling to check in on a neighbor. An example: I got a letter from my granddaughter with a poem and a paper cutout of her body with her arms stretched out to give me a hug. I bet you know someone who would love to receive a hug from you. Let me know and I will send you the poem. After you do something for someone, fill out this survey and say you are from Kelliher FCCLA. Let's flood the survey’s from our Mustang Nation.
https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/26LWFMM

post_text: Before the sun is up on school days, Kelliher drivers load coolers with food bags into vehicles for delivery to students. A total of 138 family stops are covered each day. Some coolers are even decorated with messages for the delivery teams!

post_text:
For all staff and students. Food and school educational material deliveries will start on Monday, March 30th. As we start distant learning.

School bus route drivers will deliver at regular times to home or morning area pickup sites, we will try to be as close to the student’s usual pickup time as possible. Monday’s delivery will not be at the late start time. Monday’s delivery will be at the student’s regular Tuesday through Friday pick up times.

Parents need to get the meals and materials consent forms into the school as soon as possible. Please call the school at 647-8286 if you have questions.

For continued updates please visit the Kelliher School website.

post_text: Our Attendance Matters campaign is in full swing. We had lots of reward winners for the month of October! We are looking to encourage positive attendance and being at school every day possible. We will be having our reward breakfast in February and that will be for students that meet our attendance goal of 95% or greater each month of the first semester. That student and their caregiver will be invited. We also will be having our family reward drawing at the end of January. This drawing will include students that meet the attendance goal each month of the first semester. Each family will be entered once. Thank you for all you do to help instill the importance of being present at school each day!

post_text:
Remembering 9-11. Kelliher school students and staff participated in a MN FCCLA (Family, Career & Community Leaders of America) Event this week. Students in grades 1-12 wrote letters to Military persons thanking them for their service. In addition, 6th grader Briana brought Stars for our Troops to attach to almost every postcard written. 244 postcards were written and will be sent off to Operation Gratitude. Operation Gratitude sends 250,000+ Care Packages each year to Deployed Troops, Veterans,
New Recruits & First Responders. Of all the items included in these Care Packages, the most
cherished are the personal letters of appreciation! #NeverForget, #mnfccla #Kelliherfccla
